-- ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Command gate — shell3.on_tool_call (YOUR ONLY POLICY GATE)
-- ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- UNSAFE BY DEFAULT: tools run with no restrictions. on_tool_call fires before
-- EVERY tool with t = { name, command, args, headless }; t.command is the bash
-- text for bash/bash_bg and NIL otherwise — guard on t.name first. Return nil
-- (run), { command = "..." } (rewrite, bash only), { argv = {...} } (runner
-- swap, bash only), { block = true, reason="" }, or { ask = "prompt",
-- reason="" } (Allow/Deny in Telegram or the web chat; declined → block).
-- t.headless is true when no human can answer an ask — subagents and cron
-- jobs always run headless, so an { ask = ... } there auto-denies with its
-- reason; branch on t.headless to block with a clearer message instead (see
-- the example). Denylists use shell3.regex (Go RE2, (?s) so .* spans
-- newlines); a handler that errors FAILS CLOSED. Full reference:
-- docs/configuration.md.
